<hw>Coomb</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>cumb</ets> a
liquid measure, perh. from LL. <ets>cumba</ets> boat, tomb of stone, fr.
Gr. <?/ hollow of a vessel, cup, boat, but cf. G. <ets>kumpf</ets>
bowl.]</ety> <def>A dry measure of four bushels, or half a
quarter.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>comb</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
